    <div class="slds-m-top_large">
		<h4>Overview</h4>
		<p>The <code>&lt;c:PEG_DisplayKPI_CMP&gt;</code> component may be used in any record
		Lightning page and is available directly in the App Builder (or Community Builder).
		It enables to display a KPI field (number, percent or currency) in a variety of graphical
        ways and possibly present a message beside via a text field.</p>
		<p>All of its behaviour is configurable via simple App Builder configuration attributes.</p>
        <ul>
            <li>Title: Label of the KPI, which may be dynamically set leveraging custom labels
            via the <code>$Label.c.CustomLabelName</code> syntax.</li>
            <li>KPI Field: API name of one of the numeric fields available on object,
                selectable via drop-down.</li>
            <li>KPI Format: display format for the KPI field, decimal, currency or percent.</li>
            <li>Label Field: optional API name of a text field to be displayed next to the KPI value.</li>
            <li>Display Mode: variety of KPI graphical display options, from a progress ring
            to a sequence of icons and colours based on the KPI value.</li>
            <li>Min/Max Values/Thresholds: depending on the display mode selected, may 
            be the min and max values of the KPI against which the KPI value is evaluated
                to determine a progress (ring and strength modes) or min / max thresholds
                triggering a change in icon / colour (other modes).</li>
            <li>Inverse Colouring: enables to invert the colouring logic. If checked high
                KPI values are set in red/orange instead of green.</li>
            <li>Debug: enables to display details about the actual values fetched by / configured
                on the component.</li>
        </ul>
        <p>Notes:</p>
        <ul>
        	<li>The component relies on the
                <a href="/docs/component-library/bundle/lightning:progressRing/documentation">
        		<code>lightning:progressRing</code></a> standard component for ring display.</li>
		</ul>
        <br/>
	</div>

